    <text id="F3523T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>George Welsh requests leave to attend to his unsettled private affairs.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Lieut. John Stewart</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-02-13">February 13th, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp near Falmouth VA</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor respectfully to request leave of absence for the space of ten
                    days to enable me to return to my home in Waynesboro, Franklin County Penna for
                    the following reasons.</p>

                <p>On entering the service in July last I left my private business in an unsettled
                    state. It is now important that it receive my attention as longer neglect may
                    result in serious loss to me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am sir very respectfully<lb/> Your <abbr expan="Obedient Servant">Obt.
                            Servt.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Geo Welsh<lb/> 1st Lieut. Comdg. Co. A 126 Regt</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
